        <div id="requirements" class="tab-content">
            <div class="section">
                <h2>Windows 11 System Requirements (2025)</h2>
                
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <strong>Important Update:</strong> Windows 11 24H2 and higher versions require additional CPU instruction support for SSE4.2 and the POPCNT instruction. This tightens compatibility further beyond the original 2021 requirements.
                </div>
                
                <h3>Hardware Requirements</h3>
                <div class="requirements-grid">
                    <div class="requirement-card">
                        <h4>Processor</h4>
                        <p>1 GHz or faster with 2 or more cores on a 64-bit processor or SoC</p>
                        <p><strong>Supported:</strong> Intel 8th generation and newer, AMD Ryzen 2000 series and newer</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="requirement-card">
                        <h4>Memory (RAM)</h4>
                        <p>4GB minimum</p>
                        <p><strong>Recommended:</strong> 8GB or more for optimal performance</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="requirement-card">
                        <h4>Storage</h4>
                        <p>64GB minimum storage space</p>
                        <p><strong>Note:</strong> Additional space required for updates and features</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="requirement-card">
                        <h4>System Firmware</h4>
                        <p>UEFI firmware with Secure Boot capability</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Security Requirements</h3>
                <div class="requirements-grid">
                    <div class="requirement-card">
                        <h4>TPM (Trusted Platform Module)</h4>
                        <p>TPM version 2.0 is required and "non-negotiable" according to Microsoft</p>
                        <p>Hardware-based security component for encryption and authentication</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="requirement-card">
                        <h4>Secure Boot</h4>
                        <p>Secure Boot must be enabled to protect against boot-level malware</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="interactive-element">
                    <h3>üîç Check Your System</h3>
                    <p>Use these tools to verify your computer's compatibility:</p>
                    <button class="btn btn-success" onclick="showCompatibilityTools()">Show Compatibility Tools</button>
                    <div id="compatibilityTools" class="hidden fade-in" style="margin-top: 20px;">
                        <div class="checklist">
                            <h4>Microsoft PC Health Check</h4>
                            <p>Download from Microsoft's website to get an official compatibility assessment.</p>
                            
                            <h4>Manual Checks</h4>
                            <div class="checklist-item">
                                <input type="checkbox" id="tpm-check">
                                <label for="tpm-check">Press Win + R, type "tpm.msc" to check TPM status</label>
                            </div>
                            <div class="checklist-item">
                                <input type="checkbox" id="secure-boot-check">
                                <label for="secure-boot-check">Run "msinfo32" to verify Secure Boot state</label>
                            </div>
                            <div class="checklist-item">
                                <input type="checkbox" id="cpu-check">
                                <label for="cpu-check">Use CPU-Z to verify processor generation and instruction sets</label>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div id="creation" class="tab-content">
            <div class="section">
                <h2>Creating Windows 11 Bootable USB</h2>
                
                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <strong>Requirements for USB Creation:</strong> USB flash drive with at least 8GB space (will be formatted, so backup any important data)
                </div>
                
                <h3>Method 1: Microsoft Media Creation Tool (Recommended)</h3>
                <div class="steps">
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Download the Tool</h4>
                        <p>Visit the Windows 11 download page and select "Download Now" under Create Windows 11 Installation Media</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Run MediaCreationTool.exe</h4>
                        <p>Run as administrator and accept the license terms</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Select Creation Options</h4>
                        <p>Choose "Create installation media (USB flash drive, DVD, or ISO file) for another PC"</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Configure Settings</h4>
                        <p>Select language, edition, and architecture (64-bit)</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Select USB Drive</h4>
                        <p>Choose "USB flash drive" and select your drive from the list</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Create Media</h4>
                        <p>Wait for the download and USB creation process to complete</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="interactive-element">
                    <h3>üì∏ Visual Guide: USB Creation Process</h3>
                    <p>Follow these visual steps to create your Windows 11 installation media:</p>
                    
                    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 20px;">
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center; border: 2px solid #0078d4;">
                            <div style="background: #e3f2fd; width: 80px; height: 60px; margin: 0 auto 10px; border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 24px;">üíª</div>
                            <h4 style="color: #0078d4; margin-bottom: 10px;">Step 1: Download Tool</h4>
                            <p style="color: #495057; font-size: 0.9em;">Visit Microsoft's Windows 11 download page and click "Download Now" under Create Windows 11 Installation Media</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center; border: 2px solid #28a745;">
                            <div style="background: #d4edda; width: 80px; height: 60px; margin: 0 auto 10px; border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 24px;">üîß</div>
                            <h4 style="color: #28a745; margin-bottom: 10px;">Step 2: Run Tool</h4>
                            <p style="color: #495057; font-size: 0.9em;">Run MediaCreationTool.exe as administrator, accept license terms, and select "Create installation media"</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center; border: 2px solid #ffc107;">
                            <div style="background: #fff8e1; width: 80px; height: 60px; margin: 0 auto 10px; border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 24px;">üíæ</div>
                            <h4 style="color: #f57f17; margin-bottom: 10px;">Step 3: Select USB</h4>
                            <p style="color: #495057; font-size: 0.9em;">Choose "USB flash drive", select your 8GB+ USB drive from the list (will be formatted!)</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div style="background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center; border: 2px solid #6f42c1;">
                            <div style="background: #f3e5ff; width: 80px; height: 60px; margin: 0 auto 10px; border-radius: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 24px;">‚è≥</div>
                            <h4 style="color: #6f42c1; margin-bottom: 10px;">Step 4: Wait</h4>
                            <p style="color: #495057; font-size: 0.9em;">Tool downloads Windows 11 (~5GB) and creates bootable USB. This takes 30-60 minutes depending on internet speed</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 15px; background: #e8f5e8; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #28a745;">
                        <h4 style="color: #155724; margin-bottom: 10px;">‚úÖ Success Indicators</h4>
                        <ul style="color: #495057; margin: 0; padding-left: 20px;">
                            <li>Tool shows "Your USB flash drive is ready"</li>
                            <li>USB drive contains folders: boot, efi, sources, support</li>
                            <li>USB drive shows as "ESD-USB" or similar name</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Method 2: Using Rufus (Alternative)</h3>
                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <strong>Advanced Option:</strong> Rufus is a free, open-source tool that can create bootable Windows 11 USB drives and bypass some compatibility requirements
                </div>
                
                <div class="troubleshooting-scenario">
                    <h4>üö® Troubleshooting: USB Creation Fails</h4>
                    <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Media Creation Tool fails to create USB</p>
                    <p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Try a different USB port (prefer USB 2.0 over 3.0 for compatibility)</li>
                        <li>Format the USB drive to FAT32 before starting</li>
                        <li>Run the tool as administrator</li>
                        <li>Temporarily disable antivirus software</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div id="installation" class="tab-content">
            <div class="section">
                <h2>Installing Windows 11 from USB</h2>
                
                <h3>Pre-Installation Preparation</h3>
                <div class="checklist">
                    <h4>Essential Preparation Steps</h4>
                    <div class="checklist-item">
                        <input type="checkbox" id="backup-data">
                        <label for="backup-data">Back up your important files to external storage</label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checklist-item">
                        <input type="checkbox" id="power-connected">
                        <label for="power-connected">Ensure stable power connection (for laptops: plug in charger)</label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checklist-item">
                        <input type="checkbox" id="product-key">
                        <label for="product-key">Have your Windows 11 product key ready (if required)</label>
                    </div>
                    <div class="checklist-item">
                        <input type="checkbox" id="disconnect-peripherals">
                        <label for="disconnect-peripherals">Disconnect unnecessary USB devices</label>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Boot Configuration</h3>
                <div class="steps">
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Insert USB Drive</h4>
                        <p>Connect the bootable USB drive to the target computer</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Access Boot Menu</h4>
                        <p>Restart and press boot menu key (typically F12, F2, Delete, or Esc) immediately after power-on</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Select USB Boot</h4>
                        <p>Choose the USB drive from the boot menu or change boot order in BIOS/UEFI settings</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>UEFI vs Legacy</h4>
                        <p>Ensure system is set to UEFI mode for Windows 11 (not Legacy/CSM mode)</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Installation Process</h3>
                <div class="steps">
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Language and Regional Settings</h4>
                        <p>Select language, time format, and keyboard preferences</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Install Now</h4>
                        <p>Click "Install now" to begin the installation process</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Product Key</h4>
                        <p>Enter product key or select "I don't have a product key" to continue</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>License Agreement</h4>
                        <p>Read and accept the Microsoft Software License Terms</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Installation Type</h4>
                        <p>Choose "Custom: Install Windows only" for clean installation</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Drive Selection</h4>
                        <p>Select the drive or partition where you want to install Windows 11</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <h4>Installation Progress</h4>
                        <p>Wait for files to copy and system to restart automatically multiple times</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="interactive-element">
                    <h3>‚ö° Quick Decision Point</h3>
                    <p>During installation, you reach the drive selection screen and see multiple partitions. What should you do for a clean install?</p>
                    <button class="btn" onclick="showDriveOptions()">Show Options</button>
                    <div id="driveOptions" class="hidden" style="margin-top: 15px;">
                        <div class="alert alert-info">
                            <p><strong>Best Practice:</strong> Delete existing partitions to create unallocated space, then let Windows create the necessary system partitions automatically. Always verify you're selecting the correct drive to avoid data loss!</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="alert alert-warning" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                            <p><strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Warning:</strong> Deleting partitions will permanently erase all data on those partitions. Always backup important files first!</p>
                        </div>
                        <div style="margin-top: 15px;">
                            <h4>Step-by-step process:</h4>
                            <ol>
                                <li>Select each existing partition on your target drive</li>
                                <li>Click "Delete" to remove the partition</li>
                                <li>Repeat until you have only "Unallocated Space"</li>
                                <li>Select the unallocated space and click "Next"</li>
                                <li>Windows will automatically create the necessary system partitions</li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div id="troubleshooting" class="tab-content">
            <div class="section">
                <h2>Common Installation Issues & Solutions</h2>
                
                <div class="troubleshooting-scenario">
                    <h4>üö® Issue: "This PC can't run Windows 11"</h4>
                    <p><strong>Cause:</strong> System doesn't meet minimum requirements (TPM 2.0, Secure Boot, supported CPU)</p>
                    <p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Enable TPM 2.0 in BIOS/UEFI settings</li>
                        <li>Enable Secure Boot</li>
                        <li>Verify processor compatibility</li>
                        <li>For advanced users: Use registry modifications (not recommended for production)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="troubleshooting-scenario">
                    <h4>üö® Issue: "Media Driver Missing"</h4>
                    <p><strong>Cause:</strong> Missing storage drivers for NVMe SSDs or RAID configurations</p>
                    <p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Change SATA mode from RAID to AHCI in BIOS</li>
                        <li>Load additional drivers during installation</li>
                        <li>Use different USB port (try USB 2.0 instead of 3.0)</li>
                        <li>Recreate installation media with official Microsoft tool</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="troubleshooting-scenario">
                    <h4>üö® Issue: USB Won't Boot</h4>
                    <p><strong>Cause:</strong> Incorrect BIOS settings or corrupted installation media</p>
                    <p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Verify UEFI mode is enabled (not Legacy)</li>
                        <li>Disable Secure Boot temporarily during installation</li>
                        <li>Try different USB ports</li>
                        <li>Recreate bootable USB with proper formatting (FAT32 for UEFI)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="interactive-element">
                    <h3>üéØ Troubleshooting Flowchart</h3>
                    <p>Follow this interactive troubleshooting guide:</p>
                    <button class="btn btn-warning" onclick="startTroubleshooting()">Start Troubleshooting</button>
                    <div id="troubleshootingFlow" class="hidden">
                        <div id="troubleshootingStep" class="alert alert-info">
                            <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Is your computer powering on and showing the Windows logo?</p>
                            <button class="btn" onclick="troubleshootingNext('yes', 'power')">Yes</button>
                            <button class="btn" onclick="troubleshootingNext('no', 'power')">No</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Advanced Troubleshooting Tools</h3>
                <div class="requirements-grid">
                    <div class="requirement-card">
                        <h4>Command Prompt (Shift + F10)</h4>
                        <p>Access command line during installation for advanced disk operations</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="requirement-card">
                        <h4>DiskPart Utility</h4>
                        <p>Manually partition drives and resolve disk-related issues</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="requirement-card">
                        <h4>System Information</h4>
                        <p>Use F1 or Help to access system information during installation</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div id="quiz" class="tab-content">
            <div class="section">
                <h2>Knowledge Assessment</h2>
                
                <div class="quiz-question">
                    <h4>1. What is the minimum USB drive size for Windows 11 installation media?</h4>
                    <div class="quiz-options">
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q1" value="4gb"> 4GB
                        </label>
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q1" value="8gb"> 8GB
                        </label>
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q1" value="16gb"> 16GB
                        </label>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="quiz-question">
                    <h4>2. Which security component is required for Windows 11?</h4>
                    <div class="quiz-options">
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q2" value="tpm1"> TPM 1.2
                        </label>
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q2" value="tpm2"> TPM 2.0
                        </label>
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q2" value="bitlocker"> BitLocker
                        </label>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="quiz-question">
                    <h4>3. What should you do if you get a "Media Driver Missing" error?</h4>
                    <div class="quiz-options">
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q3" value="ignore"> Ignore and continue
                        </label>
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q3" value="sata"> Change SATA mode from RAID to AHCI
                        </label>
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q3" value="format"> Format the hard drive
                        </label>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="quiz-question">
                    <h4>4. Which boot mode is required for Windows 11?</h4>
                    <div class="quiz-options">
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q4" value="legacy"> Legacy BIOS
                        </label>
                        <label class="quiz-option">
                            <input type="radio" name="q4" value="uefi"> UEFI
                        </label>
                        <label class="quiz-option">
